    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT368-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">varaivu malinta tōḻikkuk kiḻatti kūṟiyatu. </p>


        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Spoken by HER to the confidante, who rejoiced about the
          [coming] marriage. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT368">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> melliya lōyē melliya lōyē</l>
          <l> naṉṉā ṇītta paḻitīr māmai</l>
          <l> vaṉpi ṉāṟṟuta lallatu ceppiṟ</l>
          <l> colla kiṟṟā melliya lōyē</l>
          <l> ciṟiyarum periyarum vāḻu mūrkkē</l>
          <l> nāḷiṭaip paṭāa naḷinīr nīttat</l>
          <l> tiṇkaraip perumaram pōlat</l>
          <l> tīti ṉilaimai muyaṅkukam palavē.</l>


        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>O you with tender nature. O you with tender nature.</l>
          <l>The blameless dark colour which has left [us] on a good day,</l>
          <l rend="indent">besides bearing [it] with fortitude, in words</l>
          <l>we cannot speak [of it], o you with tender nature.</l>
          <l>To the village [only], where small ones and great ones are living. </l>
          <l rend="indent">Like a big tree the firm shore </l>
          <l rend="indent2">in the flood of plentiful water, without interruption ,</l>
          <l>in a faultless state we shall embrace for many [days]. </l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
